cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.CE 

This paper is primarily focused on the security of a cryptographic protocol for RFID systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of the complexity of decoding non-linear codes, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The protocol being analyzed is a communication protocol, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY) and communication and networking (cs.CE).
